net.zerobandwidth.android.lib.services

Class SingletonService.Connection

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.zerobandwidth.android.lib.services.SimpleServiceConnection<SingletonService>
      • net.zerobandwidth.android.lib.services.SingletonService.Connection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ServiceConnection, SingletonServiceInterface
    Enclosing class:
    SingletonService

    public static class SingletonService.Connection
extends SimpleServiceConnection<SingletonService>
implements android.content.ServiceConnection, SingletonServiceInterface
    A canonical implementation of the ServiceConnection interface, which simply acts as a pass-through for the public methods of the service itself. A consumer of the service does not have to implement its own ServiceConnection; instead, it may store this one and interact with it directly as if it were the service instance itself.
    Since:
    zerobandwidth-net/android 0.0.1 (#1)
